  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>cauliflower<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span> wedges&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/baharat-roasted-cauliflower-with-lentil-pilaf/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cauliflower wedges</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) and drizzle them very generously with <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sprinkle over the <strong>baharat</strong> and season them with a generous pinch of <strong>salt&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Massage the<strong> baharat</strong> and <strong>olive oil</strong> into the <strong>cauliflower wedges</strong> until they're fully coated in all the spices</p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/baharat-roasted-cauliflower-with-lentil-pilaf/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Drain and rinse the <strong>can of&nbsp;lentils</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 400ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [800ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/baharat-roasted-cauliflower-with-lentil-pilaf/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>basmati rice</strong>, <strong>ground allspice</strong>, <strong>cinnamon</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;ground coriander</strong>, <strong>turmeric</strong> and <strong>cumin seeds</strong> and cook for 30 sec or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/baharat-roasted-cauliflower-with-lentil-pilaf/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained lentils</strong> with the <strong>vegetable stock</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving &ndash; this is your <strong>lentil pilaf</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/baharat-roasted-cauliflower-with-lentil-pilaf/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>tahini</strong>&nbsp;with the juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong>, 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong> and 1 1/2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [3 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Whisk to combine and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; this is your <strong>tahini sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/baharat-roasted-cauliflower-with-lentil-pilaf/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>dill</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\r\n<p>Cut the remaining <strong>lemon</strong> into wedges</p>\r\n<p>Once the <strong>lentil pilaf</strong> is done, add the<strong> chopped parsley</strong>, season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and fluff everything together with a fork&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/baharat-roasted-cauliflower-with-lentil-pilaf/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>baharat roasted cauliflower</strong> over the<strong> lentil pilaf</strong></p>\r\n<p>Garnish with the<strong> chopped dill</strong> and<strong> crispy onions</strong></p>\r\n<p>Drizzle the <strong>tahini sauce</strong> all over&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
